---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Claudia — How it works">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="reveal font-mono text-xs text-vermillion tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">How it works</p>
      <h1 class="reveal text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-[-0.03em] leading-[1.05]">
        No settings to learn.<br />No config to write.
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal mt-5 text-paper/40 text-lg font-light max-w-lg">
        Install Claudia, open Claude Code, start building. She reads the same docs you'd read — except she's already read all of them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-28 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-white/[0.06] rounded-xl overflow-hidden stagger">
        <a href="#getting-started" class="reveal group bg-void p-8 block">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 group-hover:text-vermillion transition-colors">
            Getting Started
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-paper/35 leading-relaxed">
            Install with one command. Working in under 30 seconds.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="#what-she-knows" class="reveal group bg-void p-8 block">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 group-hover:text-vermillion transition-colors">
            What She Knows
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-paper/35 leading-relaxed">
            10 topics — databases, security, infrastructure, frontend, APIs, testing, performance, devops, data, and prompts.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="#what-she-catches" class="reveal group bg-void p-8 block">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 group-hover:text-vermillion transition-colors">
            What She Catches
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-paper/35 leading-relaxed">
            7 automatic checks — leaked secrets, bad patterns, broken dependencies, Docker issues, and more.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="#customization" class="reveal group bg-void p-8 block">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 group-hover:text-vermillion transition-colors">
            Customization
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-paper/35 leading-relaxed">
            Dial her up or down. Quiet mode, default mode, or full mentor mode. Per-project overrides.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/contribute" class="reveal group bg-void p-8 block sm:col-span-2">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper/90 group-hover:text-vermillion transition-colors">
            Help Make Her Smarter
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-paper/35 leading-relaxed">
            Contributing to Claudia means writing markdown. If you know something about a technology, you can teach it to her.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.015] rounded-xl p-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-medium text-paper/70">Want to see everything?</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-paper/30 mt-1">Every knowledge file and hook script is open source on GitHub.</p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/reganomalley/claudia"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-paper/50 hover:text-vermillion transition-colors shrink-0"
        >
          Browse the source
          <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
